        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 3:18PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Rock Falls, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nelson, Harmon, Dixon, and Woodland Shores.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
